{"title":"Pink Switchblade is a Limited Edition Homage to the Original Sun Eagle Talon","link":"https://bikerumor.com/pink-switchblade-limited-edition-original-sun-eagle-talon-mtb/","date":1707206460000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-Switchblade-launch-2024-first-ride-review-photo-c-Jens-Staudt-06.jpg\" alt=\"Pivot Switchblade Talon 35th anniversary edition next to Sun Eagle Talon\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-Switchblade-launch-2024-first-ride-review-photo-c-Jens-Staudt-06.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-Switchblade-launch-2024-first-ride-review-photo-c-Jens-Staudt-06-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-Switchblade-launch-2024-first-ride-review-photo-c-Jens-Staudt-06-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-Switchblade-launch-2024-first-ride-review-photo-c-Jens-Staudt-06-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-Switchblade-launch-2024-first-ride-review-photo-c-Jens-Staudt-06-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-Switchblade-launch-2024-first-ride-review-photo-c-Jens-Staudt-06-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-Switchblade-launch-2024-first-ride-review-photo-c-Jens-Staudt-06-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>35 years ago, Chris Colalis planted the seeds that would eventually give rise to Pivot Cycles. Only back then, it was with a fledgling bike company started by Alan Vaughn called Sun Eagle Bicycle Works. It was here that Cocalis would learn how to build frames with help from Vaughn, which yielded the Sun Eagle Talon. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-factory-tour-bikerumor-241.jpg\" alt=\"Chris Cocalis holding his Sun Eagle Talon\n\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-factory-tour-bikerumor-241.jpg 1000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-factory-tour-bikerumor-241-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-factory-tour-bikerumor-241-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-factory-tour-bikerumor-241-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-factory-tour-bikerumor-241-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-factory-tour-bikerumor-241-720x480.jpg 720w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t<figcaption>Chris Cocalis holding his Talon frame from a prior visit to Pivot HQ (Photo/Bikerumor)</figcaption>        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"Chris Cocalis holding his Sun Eagle Talon\n\" /><figcaption>Chris Cocalis holding his Talon frame from a prior visit to Pivot HQ (Photo/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"Chris Cocalis holding his Sun Eagle Talon\n\" /><figcaption>Chris Cocalis holding his Talon frame from a prior visit to Pivot HQ (Photo/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>At the time, the frame was (and still is) a wild design with elevated chainstays that essentially connected to the head tube, and a top tube that didn’t actually reach the head tube. The pink frame shown above is production frame #2 according to MOMBAT, and was built by Alan Vaughn and Chris Cocalis. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-Switchblade-launch-2024-first-ride-review-photo-c-Jens-Staudt-084-800x533.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-Switchblade-launch-2024-first-ride-review-photo-c-Jens-Staudt-084-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Pivot-